@import ./_tui.convo

> user
Add more robust mouse support.

Goals:
- Extend TUI event types to support mouse release, drag, and wheel scrolling.
- Parse SGR mouse mode events for press, release, drag, and wheel actions.
- Dispatch events to the sprite under the mouse when appropriate.
- Use wheel events to scroll scrollable sprites.
- Preserve existing click behavior.

Acceptance criteria:
- Existing click behavior still works.
- Mouse release events can be handled by sprites.
- Drag events can be handled by sprites.
- Wheel up/down scrolls the sprite under the mouse when scrollable.
- Event objects include terminal-relative x/y coordinates.
- Notes describe any intentionally deferred mouse edge cases.

